cms_content.name: Twenty Ninth Street

cms_content.name: Old Orchard

cms_content.description: Thayer St.

(All pencil sale proceeds go to 826 Boston, a nonprofit that helps students aged 6–18 find their inner authors and sharpen their writing skills.) You will also find glasses, sunglasses, books...all that good stuff.

cms_content.name: West 3rd St.

cms_content.name: Downtown Summerlin

cms_content.name: Warby Parker Frame Studio

cms_content.name: Pinecrest

cms_content.name: Pasadena

cms_content.name: Wynwood

cms_content.description: Our vibrant store at Oxmoor Center celebrates the city’s musical history with custom artwork by local illustrator Jeremy Booth.
cms_content.name: Oxmoor Center

cms_content.description: With custom blue terrazzo tiling and white oak open shelving, our second Arizona store celebrates the city’s energy and sunshine. Just take a peek at Zack Rosebrugh’s mural inspired by outside life in Scottsdale.
cms_content.name: Scottsdale Fashion Square

cms_content.description: Our charming Georgetown store features chevron wood flooring, banquette seating for reading and relaxing—and some pretty great artwork by Jason Munn.
cms_content.name: Georgetown

cms_content.description: For our first-ever New Jersey store, we worked with illustrator Ping Zhu to create amusing murals, featuring her playful palette and lively brushstrokes.
cms_content.name: Garden State Plaza

cms_content.description: Our store at the Pru features an original mural by Jason Munn and custom wallpaper illustrating all our favorite reading positions, from the Inchworm to the Awkward Dad. (Try one out on the comfy leather seating by the doors.)
cms_content.name: Prudential Center

cms_content.description: Our N. 6th store is easy to spot from a distance, thanks to the two-story mural that graffiti and sign-painting legend Stephen Powers created for the exterior. There’s even more original art from him inside. Come have a look around, and maybe find your new favorite frames.
cms_content.name: N. 6th St.

cms_content.description: The bright blue artwork inside of our Columbus Ave. store was created just for the space by New York-based illustrator JooHee Yoon. It paints a part-bird’s-eye, part-below-ground picture of the Upper West Side.
cms_content.name: Columbus Ave.

callout.intro_text: An optometrist is available to provide eye exams, and opticians are on hand to help fit and adjust your Warby Parker frames. Next-day service is available for some optical prescriptions; ask a retail advisor if your order is eligible.

cms_content.description: Our store is surrounded by cobblestone streets, century-old warehouses, and the High Line park.
cms_content.name: Washington St.

callout.intro_text: An optometrist is available to provide eye exams, and opticians are on hand to help fit and adjust your Warby Parker frames. Next-day service is available for some optical prescriptions; ask a retail advisor if your order is eligible.

cms_content.description: Our flagship retail store is located in SoHo’s historic Cast Iron District. Inspired by classic libraries, the space is lined with books (and rolling library ladders!).
cms_content.name: Greene St.

cms_content.description: The ever-ingenious Kevin Lyons created a cast of oddball characters to decorate the walls of our King of Prussia store. Come meet them (and maybe your next favorite pair, while you’re at it).
cms_content.name: King of Prussia

cms_content.description: Tucked inside our Grand Central Terminal location is the first-of-its-kind Warby Parker Solarium, an illuminated nook specially made for trying on sunglasses. This bright spot combined with a dozen colorful Marleigh Culver murals make this store a cheerful oasis for city dwellers, commuters, and far-flung visitors alike.
cms_content.name: Grand Central

cms_content.description: Stroll downtown Walnut Creek’s tree-lined streets and find us in the historic Dole House. We’ve added a few unmistakably Warby details to the original Italianate style: open oak eyewear displays, warm brass finishes, and a custom mural by Rafael Lopez.
cms_content.name: Walnut Creek

cms_content.description: Inside and out of our Chestnut Hill store, you’ll find a range of custom pieces: murals of goggling eyes and grinning mouths, “Nice to See You” stamped high above the Reference Desk, and even a glasses-shaped bike rack.
cms_content.name: The Street at Chestnut Hill

cms_content.description: King St.
